      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but even if they say they are being objective, isn't it true that focusing on what people thought in the 1700s or 1800s essentially locks in the biases and social hierarchies of those times? like, if originalism is the \"correct\" way to interpret, doesn't that just mean we're forced to follow an outdated moral framework instead of evolving with modern standards of justice and equality?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
